{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Prevent enforcement of school uniforms if temperatures exceed a certain level",
        "additional_details": "Many students find it extremely difficult to concentrate and get work completed when it is too hot, especially when they are also required to wear a school uniform, which might not be suitable for hot weather.\r\n \r\nThe Government should make it so that schools cannot require their students to wear a full school uniform if temperatures exceed a certain level, to be set following consultation with the education sector and students.",
        "background": "I would like the Government to make it so that if temperatures rise above a certain level, Primary and Secondary School should not have to wear full school uniform.",
